cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Grand-to-Ground in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "Grand-to-Ground (G2G): An adversarial, Lakatos-inspired research loop for AI-assisted social science"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Ma"
    given-names: "Rick"
    alias: "Hongtao Ma"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-07-13
url: "https://github.com/HongtaoMa1/grand-to-ground"
repository-code: "https://github.com/HongtaoMa1/grand-to-ground"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - research methodology
  - social science
  - economics
  - multi-agent systems
  - adversarial review
  - Lakatos
abstract: >-
  Grand-to-Ground (G2G) is a research methodology, packaged as a Claude plugin,
  for AI-assisted research in lab-free, deduction-first disciplines. It treats
  the researcher's grand theoretical framework as a question generator and
  converges each cycle onto one identifiable, falsifiable question via
  formalization, axiom-protected deduction, an isolated three-critic adversarial
  tribunal with anti-sycophancy quotas, empirical grounding, and scored stopping
  rules — with the human researcher as final arbiter.
